  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Validation evidence is drawn from a comprehensive observational hemolysis study conducted across five clinical sites, tracking pump-induced hemolysis indices in patients undergoing CPB. The study recorded inlet/outlet pressures, flow rates, and plasma-free hemoglobin levels under real-world operating conditions, providing a rich dataset for model comparison. The breadth of patient data and the rigorous statistical analysis of relative hemolysis indices are cited throughout the credibility argument as the primary empirical basis for accepting the CFD model predictions.",
