    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/cpb-hemolysis-decision-01",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels at MRL 2. The six non-assessed factors are appropriately scoped out per ASME V&V 40 guidance for Class II devices at MRL 2. The CFD hemolysis model is judged credible for identifying worst-case operating conditions and supporting the RH < 1 acceptance criterion relative to the predicate device. The multi-site observational hemolysis dataset provides extensive empirical coverage of the operating envelope and is considered sufficient to support the validation claim given the breadth of patient data and the rigorous statistical comparison methodology employed.",
